<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE comps PUBLIC "-//Red Hat, Inc.//DTD Comps info//EN" "comps.dtd">
<comps>
  <!--
    Note: The anaconda-tools group lists packages that anaconda might
    add to the installed package set, depending on the installation
    configuration chosen: the packages in this group are included in
    the DVD package payload and the live images, but not in the runtime
    anaconda environment. If a package is needed in anaconda's runtime
    environment it should be listed as a dependency of the anaconda
    package or pulled in via lorax, not added to this group. See
    https://fedorahosted.org/rel-eng/ticket/5195 .

    To clarify, this group is installed on the live media rather
    than provided as a repo. Assuring when Anaconda runs the second time
    from the live media, it has the packages needed to complete the
    installation. As a side effect, packages marked "mandatory" and "normal"
    then are then installed during the next upgrade cycle even if they
    were excluded from the live media.

    The solution is to mark packages which shouldn't be installed on the
    live media as "optional". This has the additional advantage that they
    don't need to be explicitly excluded in the live kickstarts. At the
    same time, pungi and the fedora build infrastructure continue to
    provide them on the DVD media repo. The latter behavior isn't well
    documented since the ability to select or deselect packages in a group
    was removed from anaconda. Yet, we now depend on that behavior in order
    to assure that all the packages in this group are provided on the DVD,
    even when a subset of the packages may conflict.
  -->
  <group>
    <id>anaconda-tools</id>
    <_name>Anaconda tools</_name>
    <_description/>
    <default>false</default>
    <uservisible>false</uservisible>
    <packagelist>
